        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Neoechiniscoides aski.Drawing of holotypicfemale (NHMD-230293),ventral view.Scale bar:50 µm.Abbreviations: an, anus; bt, buccal tube; cE, cirrus E; cm, claw membrane; ec, external cirrus; ey, eye; go, gonopore; ic, internal cirrus; lc, lateral cirrus (cirrus A); ma, lateral attachment sites associated with the female gonopore; mg, midgut; nc, new claws forming inside claw gland; oo, oocyte; ov, ovary; p1–p3, sensory structures of legs I–III, respectively; pa, ventral cuticular plate; pb, pharyngeal bulb; pc, primary clava; pl, placoid; sc, secondary clava; wl, lateral wing of the anal structure." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4623679/files/figure.png" .

